Analysis of S-layers crystallization kinetics monitored with tr-SAXS¶

Jonathan Hermann, Frdric Poitevin, ...

We consider here time-series collected after addition of Calcium on RsaA monomers, thus following the subsequent crystallization process. We aim at extracting the underlying components of the SAXS profiles, and their evolution with time.

Theoretical background¶

PCA¶

We start by performing the PCA of the data to identify how many components we expect to find. Noting $I$ the sampled intensity function, $C$ its covariance whose eigenvectors $U_{k}(q)$ are associated with the eigenvalues $\sigma^{2}_{k}$ stored in matrix $D$. The singular value decomposition of $I$ explicitely gives its expansion on the basis of the principal components: $$C(q,q') \propto \sum_{t}I(q,t)I(q',t) = UDU^{T}$$ $$I(q,t) = \sum_{k}\sigma_{k}v_{k}(t)U_{k}(q) = U\Sigma V^{T}$$ It appears that the first PC explains most of the data, and that most of the remaining information is explained by the second component. From their population profile, any component after the third one included is mostly noise. We will use this to denoise the data, by projecting it on the two first components, and proceed to find the individual components below. This just amounts to keeping the first $L$ (two here) components, so that: $$C(q,q') \approx C_{L}(q,q') \propto U_{L}D_{L}U_{L}^{T}$$ $$I(q,t) \approx I_{denoised}(q,t) = \sum_{k}^{L}\sigma_{k}v_{k}(t)U_{k}(q) = U_{L}\Sigma_{L} V_{L}^{T}$$

ICA¶

Here we look for independent components $S(q)$ in the data, by considering the following mixture $$I_{denoised}(q,t) = \sum_{k}A_{k}(t)S_{k}(q)$$

tICA¶

(see MSMbuilder for a cool explanation)

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
from matplotlib import cm
import numpy as np
from numpy import genfromtxt
from sklearn.decomposition import FastICA, PCA
from msmbuilder.decomposition import tICA

### FUNCTIONS ###
def load_data(conc,qmin_frac,qmax_frac,tmin_frac,tmax_frac):
    # Loading raw data
    filename='../data/'+str(conc)+'_q.csv'
    raw_q = genfromtxt(filename,delimiter=',')
    filename='../data/'+str(conc)+'_t.csv'
    raw_t = genfromtxt(filename,delimiter=',')
    filename='../data/'+str(conc)+'_array.csv'
    raw_data = genfromtxt(filename, delimiter=',')
    print("Raw data size (q,t,I(q,t),min(I),max(I)) = ",raw_q.shape,raw_t.shape,raw_data.shape,np.min(raw_data),np.max(raw_data))
    # Preparing work data
    qlen = len(raw_q)
    qmin = int(qlen*qmin_frac) 
    qmax = int(qlen*qmax_frac) 
    tlen = len(raw_t)
    tmin = int(tlen*tmin_frac)
    tmax = int(tlen*tmax_frac) 
    q = raw_q[qmin:qmax]
    t = raw_t[tmin:tmax]
    data = np.log(raw_data[qmin:qmax,tmin:tmax])
    print("New data size (q,t,I(q,t),min(I),max(I)) = ",q.shape,t.shape,data.shape,np.min(data),np.max(data))
    q_axis_label = 'q (inverse A)'
    t_axis_label = 't (s)'
    #
    return raw_q,raw_t,raw_data,q,t,data,q_axis_label,t_axis_label 
    
#
def plot_data(raw_q,raw_t,raw_data,q,t,data,q_axis_label,t_axis_label):
    levels1 = np.arange(0,np.min(data),0.1)
    levels2 = np.arange(np.min(data),np.max(data),0.1)
    levels3 = np.arange(np.max(data),np.log(np.max(raw_data)),0.1)
    raw_extent=[np.min(raw_q),np.max(raw_q),np.max(raw_t),np.min(raw_t)]
    extent=[np.min(q),np.max(q),np.max(t),np.min(t)]
    origin='upper'
    raw_aspect=max(raw_q)/max(raw_t)
    aspect=max(q)/max(t)
    plt.figure(figsize=(18, 8), dpi= 80, facecolor='w', edgecolor='k')
    #
    plt.subplot(121)
    plt.title('time-resolved SAXS (raw) data')
    plt.xlabel(q_axis_label)
    plt.ylabel(t_axis_label)
    plt.imshow(np.log(raw_data.T), cmap='seismic',vmin=0,vmax=np.log(np.max(raw_data)),origin=origin,extent=raw_extent,aspect=raw_aspect)
    plt.colorbar()
    plt.contour(np.log(raw_data.T), levels1, linewidths=0.2,colors='k', origin=origin,extent=raw_extent)
    plt.contour(np.log(raw_data.T), levels2, linewidths=1,colors='k', origin=origin,extent=raw_extent)
    plt.contour(np.log(raw_data.T), levels3, linewidths=0.2,colors='k', origin=origin,extent=raw_extent)
    #
    plt.subplot(122)
    plt.title('time-resolved SAXS (working) data')
    plt.xlabel(q_axis_label)
    plt.ylabel(t_axis_label)
    plt.imshow(data.T, cmap='seismic',vmin=np.min(data),vmax=np.max(data),origin=origin,extent=extent,aspect=aspect)
    plt.colorbar()
    plt.contour(data.T, levels1, linewidths=0.2,colors='k', origin=origin,extent=extent)
    plt.contour(data.T, levels2, linewidths=1,colors='k', origin=origin,extent=extent)
    plt.contour(data.T, levels3, linewidths=0.2,colors='k', origin=origin,extent=extent)
    #
    print('The data is shown above on a log scale contoured in steps of 1/10, with an emphasis on the area that see Bragg peaks appearing with time.')
    #
    plt.show()
#
def do_analysis(data,nPCs_compute,nPCs,nICs,ntICs_compute,ntICs,lagtime):
    ########
    # PCA
    pca = PCA(n_components=nPCs_compute)
    H = pca.fit_transform(data.T)  
    variance_ratio = pca.explained_variance_ratio_
    # 2nd round on first components only
    pca = PCA(n_components=nPCs)
    H = pca.fit_transform(data.T)
    eigenval = pca.singular_values_[0:nPCs]
    weights = pca.transform(data.T)
    eigenvec = pca.components_.T
    meanvec  = pca.mean_
    denoised = (meanvec + np.dot(eigenvec,weights.T).T).T
    # ICA
    input_data = denoised # data
    ica = FastICA(n_components=nICs,algorithm='parallel',fun="logcosh")
    S_ = ica.fit_transform(input_data)  # Reconstruct signals
    A_ = ica.mixing_  # Get estimated mixing matrix
    # tICA (http://msmbuilder.org/development/examples/tICA-vs-PCA.html)
    input_data = denoised # data
    tica = tICA(n_components=ntICs_compute, kinetic_mapping=True,lag_time=lagtime)
    tica.fit([input_data.T])
    tica_eigenval = tica.eigenvalues_
    tica_eigenvec = tica.components_.T[:,0:ntICs]
    tica_weights  = tica.transform([input_data.T])[0]
    #
    return eigenval,eigenvec, weights, meanvec,denoised,S_,A_,tica_eigenval,tica_eigenvec,tica_weights
    #########
#
def plot_analysis(q,t,data,eigenval,eigenvec, weights, meanvec,denoised,S_,A_,tica_eigenval,tica_eigenvec,tica_weights,nPCs_compute,nPCs,nICs,ntICs_compute,ntICs,q_axis_label,t_axis_label):
    ### PCA with nPCs_compute components, only show nPCs first ones
    initvec  = data.T[0,:]
    endvec   = data.T[len(t)-1,:]
    Plabels = []
    for i in np.arange(0,nPCs,1):
        Plabels.append('PC'+str(i+1))
    Ilabels=[]
    for i in np.arange(0,nICs,1):
        Ilabels.append('IC'+str(i+1))
    tIlabels=[]
    for i in np.arange(0,ntICs,1):
        tIlabels.append('tIC'+str(i+1))
    #
    nrow=7
    ncol=3
    plt.figure(figsize=(18, 28), dpi= 80, facecolor='w', edgecolor='k')
    #DATA BLOCK
    plt.subplot(nrow,ncol,1)
    plt.grid()
    plt.title('First, last and average exp. SAXS profiles')
    plt.xlabel(q_axis_label)
    plt.ylabel('Initial and final (dashed), and average (plain black) profiles')
    plt.plot(q,initvec, 'k--')
    plt.plot(q,endvec, 'k--')
    plt.plot(q,meanvec, color='black')
        #
    plt.subplot(nrow,ncol,2)
    plt.grid()
    plt.title('Denoised data (demeaned)')
    plt.xlabel(q_axis_label)
    plt.ylabel('I_denoised(iq,it)')
    for i in np.arange(0,int(len(t)),1):
        plt.plot(q,denoised[:,i]-meanvec)
    #
    plt.subplot(nrow,ncol,3)
    plt.grid()
    plt.title('Remaining data')
    plt.xlabel(q_axis_label)
    plt.ylabel('I(iq,it) - I_denoised(iq,it)')
    plt.plot(q,data-denoised)
    ####
    # PCA BLOCK
    plt.subplot(nrow,ncol,4)
    plt.grid()
    plt.title('Variance ratio explained by PC')
    plt.xlabel('PC ID')
    plt.ylabel('variance ratio')
    plt.ylim(-0.1,1.1)
    plt.plot(variance_ratio, 'ko')
    plt.plot(np.cumsum(variance_ratio), 'k-')
    #
    plt.subplot(nrow,ncol,5)
    plt.grid()
    plt.title('Population of PCs over time (recentered on initial profile)')
    plt.xlabel(t_axis_label)
    plt.ylabel('s(PC)*v(PC,t)')
    for i in np.arange(0,nPCs,1):
        wzero = weights[0,i]
        plt.plot(t,weights[:,i]-wzero, label=Plabels[i])
    plt.legend()
    #
    plt.subplot(nrow,ncol,6)
    plt.grid()
    plt.title('SAXS profile of individual PCs ')
    plt.xlabel(q_axis_label)
    plt.ylabel('U(PC,q)')
    for i in np.arange(0,nPCs,1):
        plt.plot(q,eigenvec[:,i] , label=Plabels[i])
    plt.legend()
    ####
    # ICA BLOCK
    plt.subplot(nrow,ncol,8)
    plt.grid()
    plt.title('Population of ICs over time (recentered on initial profile)')
    plt.xlabel(t_axis_label)
    plt.ylabel('A(IC,t)')
    for y_arr, label in zip(A_.T, Ilabels):
        yzero = y_arr[0]
        plt.plot(t, y_arr - yzero, label=label)
        #print(label,np.max(y_arr) - np.min(y_arr))
    plt.legend()
    #
    plt.subplot(nrow,ncol,9)
    plt.grid()
    plt.title('SAXS profile of individual ICs')
    plt.xlabel(q_axis_label)
    plt.ylabel('S(IC,q)')
    for y_arr, label in zip(S_.T, Ilabels):
        plt.plot(q, y_arr , label=label)
    plt.legend()
    ####
    # tICA BLOCK
    plt.subplot(nrow,ncol,10)
    plt.grid()
    plt.title('eigenval tIC')
    plt.xlabel('tIC ID')
    plt.ylabel('eigenval')
    plt.plot(tica_eigenval, 'ko')
    #
    plt.subplot(nrow,ncol,11)
    plt.grid()
    plt.title('evolution of individaul tICs ')
    plt.xlabel('it')
    plt.ylabel('P(tIC,t)')
    for i in np.arange(0,ntICs,1):
        wzero = tica_weights[0,i]
        plt.plot(tica_weights[:,i]-wzero , label=tIlabels[i])
    plt.legend()
    #
    plt.subplot(nrow,ncol,12)
    plt.grid()
    plt.title('SAXS profile of individual tICs ')
    plt.xlabel('iq')
    plt.ylabel('I(IC,q)')
    for i in np.arange(0,ntICs,1):
        plt.plot(tica_eigenval[i]*tica_eigenvec[:,i] , label=tIlabels[i])
    plt.legend()
    #
    n=13
    for i in np.arange(0,nPCs,1):
        plt.subplot(nrow,ncol,n)
        plt.title('projection on PCs over time')
        plt.grid()
        proj=np.outer(eigenvec[:,i], weights[:,i].T)
        for j in np.arange(0,int(len(t)),1):
            proj_zero=proj[:,0]
            plt.plot(q,proj[:,j]-proj_zero)
        n=n+1
    n=16
    for i in np.arange(0,nICs,1):
        plt.subplot(nrow,ncol,n)
        plt.title('projection on ICs over time')
        plt.grid()
        proj=np.outer(S_[:,i], A_[:,i].T)
        for j in np.arange(0,int(len(t)),1):
            proj_zero=proj[:,0]
            plt.plot(q,proj[:,j]-proj_zero)
        n=n+1
    n=19
    for i in np.arange(0,ntICs,1):
        plt.subplot(nrow,ncol,n)
        plt.title('projection on tICs over time')
        plt.grid()
        proj=np.outer(tica_eigenvec[:,i], tica_weights[:,i].T)
        for j in np.arange(0,int(len(t)),1):
            proj_zero=proj[:,0]
            plt.plot(q,proj[:,j]-proj_zero)
        n=n+1
    #
    plt.show()
